cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.LO. 

The paper deals with reasoning with knowledge expressed in natural language and Knowledge Bases (KBs), which is a major challenge for Artificial Intelligence. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes a novel approach for jointly reasoning over KBs and textual mentions, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.DB (Databases) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
